 ```latex
\begin{figure}[h]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=\textwidth]{path_to_your_image.png}
    \caption{Caption here}
    \label{fig:default_default_1}
\end{figure}
```
In the code snippet above, replace `path_to_your_image.png` with the path to your image file on your computer or in your project directory. This is a standard LaTeX figure environment setup for an inline figure with a caption and label for easy reference within the document.

 ```latex
\begin{figure}[h!]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=\linewidth]{path_to_your_image.png}
    \caption{Caption here}
    \label{fig:default_default_1}
\end{figure}
```

This code will place the figure at the desired location in your LaTeX document, center it, and include the image from the specified path with a given caption and label. The "h!" parameter means that this figure should be placed here if possible, but not float to another page. Replace `path_to_your_image.png` with the actual path to your image file in your project's directory.
